OL,3,CGovernment announces concessions to
OL,4,Cwelfare bill after talks
OL,6,FThe announcement comes after crisis
OL,7,Ftalks with backbenchers, with some 126
OL,8,FMPs within the party signing an
OL,9,Famendment that would halt the
OL,10,Flegislation in its tracks.
OL,12,FSir Keir Starmer's Universal Credit
OL,13,Fand Personal Independence Payment Bill
OL,14,Fhas its second reading on Tuesday, the
OL,15,Ffirst opportunity for MPs to support
OL,16,For reject it.
